Hebrews 2-7 <t>You made him for a little while lower than the angels; </t><t>you have crowned him with glory and honor, <f>[1]</f></t>
Hebrews 2-8 <t>putting everything in subjection under his feet.” </t> <pb/>Now in putting everything in subjection to him, he left nothing outside his control. At present, <f>ⓞ</f>we do not yet see everything in subjection to him.
Hebrews 2-9 But we see him <f>ⓟ</f>who for a little while was made lower than the angels, namely Jesus, <f>ⓠ</f>crowned with glory and honor <f>ⓡ</f>because of the suffering of death, so that by the grace of God he might <f>ⓢ</f>taste death <f>ⓣ</f>for everyone.
Hebrews 2-10 <pb/>For it <f>ⓤ</f>was fitting that he, <f>ⓥ</f>for whom and by whom all things exist, in bringing many sons <f>ⓦ</f>to glory, should make the <f>ⓧ</f>founder of their salvation <f>ⓨ</f>perfect through suffering.
Hebrews 2-11 For <f>ⓩ</f>he who sanctifies and <f>ⓐ</f>those who are sanctified <f>ⓑ</f>all have one source. <f>[2]</f> That is why he is not ashamed to call them <f>ⓒ</f>brothers, <f>[3]</f>
